"v.泄露，透露 【英】 v. 泄露，透露(to make known; disclose) 【考】 反义词：keep secret(保密) 【记】 di+vulge(普通)→使 …普通→透露 【同】 同根词: vulgar(粗俗的, 普通的) 【例】 Betraying a confidence, John divulged the secret to others. v. 泄露, 透露(秘密, 隐私等) = disclose 【记】di向四面八方, vulge普通大众－散发给大众－透露读: 待我知－有待于让我知道, 说明有人会透露给我 【参】vulgar(adj 粗俗的; 普通的; 本土的) 【反】keep secret(保密) 【记】前面象reveal；dis 向四周 + vulgar 大众的，粗俗的，make public 让大众都知道 【相关】vulgar 大众的，粗俗的 divulge (v.)  mid-15c., from Latin divulgare ""publish, make common,"" from dis- ""apart"" (see dis-) + vulgare ""make common property,"" from vulgus ""common people"" (see vulgar). Related: Divulged; divulging."
